{"title_page": "Erika Jayne", "text_new": "{{short description|American singer, actress and television personality}}\n{{Advert|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Erika Jayne\n| image              = File:Erika_Jayne.jpg\n| alt                = photo of Erika Jayne\n| caption            = Erika Jayne signing autographs in [[New York City]] on March 2, 2020 after a performance of the ''[[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]]'' musical.\n| birth_name         = Erika Nay Chahoy\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1971|07|10}}\n| birth_place        = [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], U.S.\n| other_names        = Erika Girardi\n| education          = North Atlanta High School for the Performing Arts\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Singer-songwriter, actress\n| years_active       = 1990\u2013present\n| television         = ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]''<br>\n''[[Dancing With the Stars]]''<br>\n''[[The Young and the Restless]]''\n| spouse             = Thomas Zizzo\n\n             {{Marriage|[[Thomas Girardi]]|1999}}\n| children           = 1\n| website            = {{URL|erikajayne.com}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| genre = {{flat list|\n* [[Club music|Club]]\n* [[Dance music|dance]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]\n}}\n| instrument = Vocals\n| label = {{flat list|\n* EJ\n* RM\n* Pretty Mess\n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flat list|\n* [[Maino]]\n* [[Flo Rida]]\n}}}}\n}}\n\n'''Erika Nay Girardi''' (n\u00e9e '''Chahoy'''; born July 10, 1971),<ref>{{cite web|work=[[BBC]] Music|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/f9c72c3c-2ebd-4b79-b8a3-b782f70cdc48|title=Erika Jayne|accessdate=May 23, 2018}}</ref> known professionally as '''Erika Jayne''', is an American singer, actress and television personality.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Agard|first1=Chancellor|title=Newest ''Beverly Hills'' Housewives Erika Girardi Teases Run-In with Bethenny Frankel: She 'Kind of Let Me Have It'|url=http://www.people.com/article/real-housewives-beverly-hills-erika-girardi-erika-jayne |website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=December 15, 2015|accessdate=December 16, 2015}}</ref> Her debut single \"[[Roller Coaster (Erika Jayne song)|Roller Coaster]]\" topped the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Dance Club Songs]] chart in 2007, she has attained nine number-one songs on the Dance Club Songs chart {{as of|2018|lc=y}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/erika-jayne/chart-history|title=Erika Jayne Chart History - Billboard : Page 1|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars/cast/erika-jayne|title=Erika Jayne {{!}} Dancing with the Stars|website=ABC|access-date=2017-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327080559/http://abc.go.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars/cast/erika-jayne|archive-date=2017-03-27|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2016, ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' ranked her number 42 on their list of greatest [[Dance Club Songs|dance club]] artists of all time and number 3 on their list of the Next Big Sound.<ref name=\":16\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-top-dance-club-artists|title=Greatest of All Time Top Dance Club Artists : Page 1|work=Billboard|access-date=2017-03-26}}</ref><ref name=\":12\" />\n\nGirardi launched her film and television career as an actress in the early 1990s, playing small roles on ''[[Law & Order]]'' and ''[[High Incident]]''. In 2015, Girardi became a full-time cast member on the sixth season of the [[reality television]] series ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]'', followed by her role on the competition series ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/this-is-how-famous-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-star-erika-jayne-is-in-other-countries-9260147|title=This Is How Famous 'Real Housewives of Beverly Hills' Star Erika Jayne Is In Other Countries|last=Witter|first=Brad|work=Bustle|access-date=2018-07-03|language=en}}</ref> She has played a recurring role as real estate agent Farrah Dubose on the American television [[soap opera]] ''[[The Young and the Restless]].''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/931519/get-ready-genoa-city-erika-girardi-is-returning-to-the-young-and-the-restless-in-a-major-way|title=Erika Girardi Is Returning to The Young and the Restless!|work=E! Online|access-date=2018-06-13|language=en-US}}</ref> She made her [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut in ''[[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]]'' as [[Roxie Hart]] on January 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorktheatreguide.com/news-features/erika-jayne-makes-her-broadway-debut-in-chicago|title=Erika Jayne makes her Broadway debut in Chicago|last=Millward|first=Tom|date=December 27, 2019|website=New York Theater Guide|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/rhobh-star-erika-jayne-in-chicago-how-tom-girardi-reacted|title=Erika Girardi Just Revealed a Major Secret About Husband Tom|date=2020-01-06|website=Bravo TV Official Site|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnewyork.com/entertainment/the-scene/new-york-live/erika-jayne-in-broadways-chicago/2255945/|title=Erika Jayne in Broadway\u2019s \u2018Chicago\u2019|website=NBC New York|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\n\n=== 1971\u20131998: Early life and career beginnings ===\nErika Girardi was born in [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] on July 10, 1971, to a single mother, Renee Chahoy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-girardi-mother-relationship|title=Erika Girardi Hopes Her Relationship with Her Mom Is Something People 'Will Be Able to Relate To' |date=2017-03-08|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2017-07-21|language=en-US}}</ref> Her mother, a fellow actress and a classically trained pianist, was only 18 when she gave birth to Girardi. Her parents broke up before her first birthday. Describing her childhood in her book ''Pretty Mess'', Girardi states that her mother was \"short with me, hard on me, and irritable. She would snatch my ponytail, dig her nails into my arm, and step on my feet. And that was in public.\"<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite news|url=https://tasteofreality.com/9-things-we-learned-from-reading-erika-jaynes-new-memoir-pretty-mess/|title=9 Things We Learned From Reading Erika Jayne's New Memoir 'Pretty Mess'|date=2018-03-30|work=Taste of Reality|access-date=2018-08-07|language=en-US}}</ref> Girardi was later adopted by her mother's new partner, and they were married and divorced twice. In the middle of the marriages, her stepfather legally adopted her, but cut off contact after the second divorce from her mother.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://radaronline.com/photos/needs-text-erika-jayne-mom-childhood-trauma-tell-all/|title=My Mom Hurt Me! RHOBH's Erika Jayne Reveals Childhood Trauma In Shocking New Tell-All|date=2018-03-14|work=RadarOnline|access-date=2018-03-22|language=en-US}}</ref> Girardi met her biological father for the first time at the age of 25 and compared it to \"meeting a stranger\".<ref name=people-interview>{{Cite news |last=Quinn |first=Dave |title=Erika Girardi Didn't Meet Her Estranged Father Until She Was 25: 'We Don't Speak' |url=http://people.com/tv/rhobh-erika-girardi-opens-up-about-estranged-father/ |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=17 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref> Girardi has revealed that she has seen her biological father only twice after their first meeting, saying \"he had never, ever acknowledged my existence, to anyone, and obviously to himself, as well.\"<ref name=et-interview>{{Cite news |last=Sander |first=Brice |date=January 2, 2018 |title='RHOBH' Star Erika Jayne Opens Up About Strained Relationship with Biological Father (Exclusive) |url=https://www.etonline.com/rhobh-star-erika-jayne-opens-about-strained-relationship-biological-father-exclusive-93388 |work=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |access-date=17 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref> Girardi has said that her tough upbringing made her grow up quickly and taught her to be self-reliant.<ref name=people-interview/> She had a close relationship with her grandparents, Hollis and Ann Peek.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://okhereisthesituation.com/2017/03/erika-jayne-opens-mother-grandmother/|title=Erika Jayne opens up about her mother and grandmother |date=2017-03-07|work=Ok! Here's the Situation - O!HitS|access-date=2017-07-21|language=en-US}}</ref> Girardi's grandfather whom she called \"the only father I've ever known\", died in July 2010 at the age of 81.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/erika-girardi-grandmother-alzheimers-disease-rhobh-recap/|title=RHOBH\u2019s Erika Girardi Breaks Down over Her Grandmother\u2019s Heartbreaking Battle with Alzheimer's Disease|date=2017-03-08|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2017-07-21|language=en-US}}</ref> Her grandmother died of [[Alzheimer's disease]] in November 2014 at the age of 86. \u201cMy grandmother and I used to speak on the phone for an hour every day about nothing. When those phone calls stopped, that was the hardest. Because I knew she could no longer communicate. I had always gotten such strength and such love from those phone calls and when they stopped, it was a real marker of, \u2018This is over, Erika. The woman that you know is no longer,\u201d she said in an episode of ''The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills''.\n\n{{Quote box\n| width = 300px\n| align = left\n| quote = My mom and dad were married, but he left when I was about nine months old. He went on and lived his life, and I did not meet my dad until I was 25. He invited me up for Thanksgiving and it was awkward for sure. [I was] basically at a stranger's house, by myself. There was this moment in my father's house, and his daughter\u2014she was a little toddler\u2014she was playing around, and I said, \"Well, how did you end up with a baby?\" And he said, \"Well, you know, my wife, she never had any kids and I never had any kids.\" And I was like, \"Yeah....\"\n|source=\u2014Girardi, on her background<ref name=et-interview/>\n}}\n\nGirardi graduated from [[North Atlanta High School]]. She enrolled in a magnet program for the performing arts in high school, saying, \"That\u2019s where you really learned to love the stage and really hone your early performing skills. I wouldn\u2019t trade that experience for anything in the world.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/13-things-you-didnt-know-about-erika-girardi|title=13 Things You Didn't Know About Erika Girardi|date=2016-01-15|newspaper=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2017-02-22|language=en-US}}</ref> She joined musical theater in high school, playing roles such as Val from ''[[A Chorus Line]]'' and Frastrada in ''[[Pippin (musical)|Pippin]]''. She toured the world in the school revue show where she performed \"[[9 to 5 (Dolly Parton song)|9 to 5]]\" by [[Dolly Parton]] and \"[[Into the Groove|Into The Groove]]\" by [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]].<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mercylounge.com/event/1768277-erika-jayne-pretty-mess-nashville/|title=Erika Jayne presents: The Pretty Mess Tour - Tickets - Cannery Ballroom - Nashville, TN - December 14th, 2018|website=Mercy Lounge|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-05}}</ref> Her first jobs in the entertainment industry included doing modelling and local commercials as a child.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/real-housewife-of-beverly-hills-erika-jayne-workwives-podcast|title='Real Housewives' Star Erika Jayne on That Time She Fired an Assistant by Leaving Her in a Hotel Room|last=Glamour|work=Glamour|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en}}</ref> At 18, she moved to [[New York City]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/rhobh-erika-girardi-painful-past-wealthy-coma/|title=Erika Girardi on Painful Past \u2014 and Realizing She Was in a 'Wealthy Coma' After Marriage|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-03-22|language=en}}</ref> She performed as a member of several girl groups while living in New York, including recording songs with ''[[The Flirts]]'' and performing with ''I-Dolls''. During this time she met Italian Thomas Zizzo, when he was working as a DJ at a club in [[Manhattan]]. The couple got married in December 1991 at [[St. Patrick's Cathedral (Manhattan)|St. Patrick's Cathedral]]. She described the wedding as \"big, obnoxious, and pink.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-erika-girardis-early-life-detailed-pretty-mess|title=7 Things We Learned About the Early Life of Pretty Mess Erika Girardi|date=2018-03-21|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-03-24|language=en-US}}</ref> Soon after she gave birth to a son, Thomas Zizzo, Jr. After the couple divorced a few years later, she relocated to [[Los Angeles]] to pursue her dream of becoming a singer and performer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bravotv.com/people/erika-girardi|title=Erika Girardi Biography |work=Bravo|publisher=Bravo TV |date= 2015|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nEarly in her career, Girardi worked as a waitress to support herself between acting jobs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-girardi-pre-fame-jobs|title=Erika Girardi Was a Pretty Mess at One of Her Pre-Fame Jobs|date=2017-03-03|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en-US}}</ref> Girardi began her acting career in the early 1990s by appearing in small roles in several American television series and films. Her first on-screen appearance was a role as Suzanne Morton in the episode \"Prescription for Death\" of [[NBC]]'s [[legal drama]] series ''[[Law & Order]].'' She played the first-ever person to die on the show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.etonline.com/erika-jaynes-pretty-mess-7-revelations-from-the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-stars-memoir-98638|title=Erika Jayne\u2019s \u2018Pretty Mess\u2019: 7 Revelations From \u2018The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills\u2019 Star\u2019s Memoir|work=Entertainment Tonight|access-date=2018-03-21|language=en}}</ref> In 1991, she made her second appearance on the show in the episode \"Violence of Summer\". She also had roles in independent films ''Alchemy'' (1995) and ''Lowball'' (1996).<ref>{{cite web|title=Low Ball (1997)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lowball_1997/|website=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=July 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Alchemy (1995)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/alchemy-1995/|website=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=July 3, 2017}}</ref> She appeared as Kitty in ''Alchemy'', playing a woman who befriends her former partner's ex-wife after his death. She portrayed a struggling single mother, Kate in the action film ''Lowball'' alongside [[Everlast (musician)|Erik Schrody]] and [[Luis Moro]].<ref name=\":6\" /> In 1997, Girardi appeared as Cindy Butterworth in an episode of the [[Police procedural|police drama]] [[Television series|series]] ''[[High Incident]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=High Incident Full Cast and Credits |url=http://www.hollywood.com/tv/high-incident-59476719/credits/|website=Hollywood|accessdate=October 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== 1999\u20132016: Debut album and television projects ===\nIn January 1999, she married attorney [[Thomas Girardi]], a founding partner of Girardi & Keese in downtown Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peasantyogi.com/blog/2016/1/26/i-interviewed-erika-fucking-jayne-from-the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202182635/http://www.peasantyogi.com/blog/2016/1/26/i-interviewed-erika-fucking-jayne-from-the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/|archivedate=February 2, 2016|url-status=dead|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref> She has discussed spending her early 30s focusing on her life with her husband, saying: \"My husband is a lawyer, and I lived a lawyer's wife's life. I was with him all the time. And then, I finally said, 'You know what? I need to go back and perform and do what I love for me,' and that's how Erika Jayne was born.\"<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-jayne-isnt-erika-girardis-only-alter-ego|title=Erika Jayne Isn't Erika Girardi's Only Alter Ego|date=2016-06-14|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-06-08|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/erika-girardi-on-music-marriage-and-rhobh-ive-become-desensitized-to-how-much-sexy-i-put-out/|title=Erika Girardi on Music, Marriage and RHOBH: 'I've Become Desensitized To How Much Sexy I Put Out'|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref> Girardi has called this period of her life \"great legal education\".<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.tipsonlifeandlove.com/love-and-relationships/erika-jayne-marriage|title=Can Marriage Survive a 30-Year Age Gap? Ask Erika Jayne - Tips on Life and Love|date=2018-03-25|work=Tips on Life and Love|access-date=2018-08-07|language=en-US}}</ref> \"I sat in so many meetings, dinners, and talks with the very best legal minds. I went to the U.S. Supreme Court to watch a session. We would go to the Senate to meet people and talk to them on an intimate level. This was not the kind of meet and greet where you shake a politician\u2019s hand and get a picture with him. No, we would have dinner with the mayor and his wife, and we\u2019d listen to what he thinks about the city\u2019s homeless problem. We would have drinks with a U.S. senator, and she\u2019d confide in us the problems the senators were having with the current administration. These were some great experiences,\" Girardi shared in her memoir, ''Pretty Mess''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tipsonlifeandlove.com/love-and-relationships/erika-jayne-marriage|title=Can Marriage Survive a 30-Year Age Gap? Ask Erika Jayne - Tips on Life and Love|date=2018-03-25|work=Tips on Life and Love|access-date=2018-10-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nStaying true to her love of music, Jayne's first dance music single \"[[Roller Coaster (Erika Jayne song)|Roller Coaster]]\" was released on January 1, 2007. The song placed at number one on the [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] [[Hot Dance Club Play]] chart. Her second single \u201c[[Stars (Erika Jayne song)|Stars]]\u201d also placed at number one the Billboard Dance Play chart and music video for the song spent 12 weeks (peaking at number 2) on [[Logo TV]]\u2019s [[The Click List: Top 10 Videos]]. In 2007, British newspaper ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that Erika Jayne \u201cis [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]] trapped in the moment when she recorded the ''[[Erotica (Madonna album)|Erotica]]'' album. She\u2019s [[Nicole Kidman]] in ''[[Moulin Rouge!|Moulin Rouge]]'' goes trance with a dash of debauchery, or [[Gwen Stefani]] goes burlesque.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2007/jun/06/popandrock|title=No 117: Erika Jayne|date=2007-06-06|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-10-27}}</ref> Jayne's debut full-length album ''[[Pretty Mess (album)|Pretty Mess]]'', was released in the United States on August 11, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Pretty-Mess-Erika-Jayne/dp/B002FKZ4VI|title=Amazon.com: Erika Jayne: Pretty Mess: Music|publisher=|accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref> [[Sheila E.]] is found playing percussion on the song, \u201cTime to Realize\u201d and the album includes a cover of [[Apollonia 6]]\u2019s 1984 hit \u201c[[Sex Shooter]].\u201d Peter Rafelson and [[Eric Kupper]] served as producers and co-writers on ''Pretty Mess'', while Canadian singer-songwriter [[Esthero]], Jahi Lake and Ike Dirty contributed additional production. The other singles from the album were \"Give You Everything\" and \"Pretty Mess\". The album spawned a total of four number-one singles on the Hot Dance Club Play chart. She released three different music video versions of \"Give You Everything\". The music videos were directed by feature film director Marty Thomas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celebrityviplounge.com/exclusive-interview-erika-jayne/ |title=\u00bb EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW: Erika Jayne - Celebrity VIP Lounge |accessdate=11 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402085928/http://celebrityviplounge.com/exclusive-interview-erika-jayne/ |archivedate=2 April 2015 }}</ref> Remixes of \"Give You Everything\" placed at number 2 on the Music Week Upfront Club Chart as well as number 6 on the Music Week Commercial Pop Club Chart, marking her first time to land on the [[United Kingdom]] charts. Jayne supported the release of ''Pretty Mess'' with tour dates and appearances at festivals and clubs across the United States. In November 2010, Jayne announced the creation of her own record label, Pretty Mess Records.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Greenberg|first1=Alexandra|title=Erika Jayne Launches Pretty Mess Records \"One Hot Pleasure\" Single Set For Label Debut Release November 16|url=http://www.msopr.com/press-releases/erika-jayne-launches-pretty-mess-records%E2%80%9Cone-hot-pleasure%E2%80%9D-single-set-for-label-debut-release-november-16/|website=Mitch Schneider Organization|accessdate=October 10, 2016|date=November 1, 2010}}</ref>\n\nHer next releases, \"[[One Hot Pleasure]]\" and \"[[Party People (Ignite the World)]]\", also reached number one on the [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] [[Hot Dance Club Play]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.erikajayne.com/news/page/7 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=December 16, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120422124219/http://www.erikajayne.com/news/page/7 |archivedate=April 22, 2012 }}</ref> \"[[Party People (Ignite the World)]]\" was written and produced by Swedish producers [[Andreas Carlsson|Andreas Carisson]] and Niclas Kings. The dance-driven music video for the single was directed and choreographed by Mikey Minden.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/erika-jayne-tops-billboards-hot-danceclub-play-songs-chart-with-new-single-party-people-ignite-the-world-136908543.html|title=Erika Jayne Tops Billboard's \"Hot Dance/Club Play Songs\" Chart With New Single \"Party People (Ignite the World)\"|last=Jayne|first=Erika|website=prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref> \"Party People (Ignite the World)\" marked her sixth number-one single on US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Dance Club Songs]] chart.<ref name=\":14\" /> That achievement landed her on a billboard on [[PR Newswire]]\u2019s building in [[Times Square]] and on the advertisement cover in ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\u2019s February 11, 2012 issue.<ref name=\":14\" /> In 2012, \"All Things Aside\", was featured in the comedy film [[The Watch (2012 film)|''The Watch'']] starring [[Ben Stiller]] and [[Vince Vaughn]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.what-song.com/Movies/Soundtrack/1050/The-Watch|title=The Watch (2012) Soundtrack and Complete List of Songs|website=What-song|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-26}}</ref> Her music has been featured in several films, including, ''The Neighbor'' (2007), ''Deal'' (2008),  ''[[Hit and Run (2009 film)|Hit and Run]]'' (2009), [[The Pool Boys|''American Summer'']] (2011)  and ''High Society'' (2017).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.last.fm/music/Erika+Jayne/+wiki|title=Erika Jayne biography {{!}} Last.fm|website=Last.fm|language=en|access-date=2018-03-03}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, she released a single featuring American rapper [[Flo Rida]], \"[[Get it Tonight (Erika Jayne song)|Get it Tonight]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.entertainment-focus.com/music-section/music-news/erika-jayne-teases-get-it-tonight/|title=Erika Jayne teases Get It Tonight - Entertainment Focus|website=entertainment-focus.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.entertainment-focus.com/music-section/music-news/erika-jayne-teases-get-it-tonight/|title=Erika Jayne teases Get It Tonight - Entertainment Focus|website=entertainment-focus.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-07}}</ref> \"Get It Tonight\" reached number 13 on the Dance/Electronic Streaming Songs chart.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/erika-jayne/chart-history/dance-electronic-streaming-songs/song/780412|title=Erika Jayne Get It Tonight Chart History|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-07-07}}</ref> The single was released through a joint venture with Pretty Mess Records and New Nation Live label, distributed by [[Universal Music Group]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Erika-Jayne-Featuring-Flo-Rida-Get-It-Tonight/release/9763173|title=Erika Jayne Featuring Flo Rida - Get It Tonight|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-08-12}}</ref> Marenah Dobin of ''[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]'' called \"Get It Tonight\" the \"perfect party song.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/erika-jayne-songs-you-should-listen-to-right-now-66740|title=Erika Jayne Songs You Should Listen To Right Now|last=Dobin|first=Marenah|work=Bustle|access-date=2018-11-05|language=en}}</ref> In September 2014, Jayne achieved her seventh number one dance single with \"PAINKILLR\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-09-28/dance-club-play-songs|title=Hot Dance Club Songs |work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |date= September 28, 2014|accessdate=September 18, 2014}}</ref> The [[Scott Storch]]-produced single \"Crazy\", featuring [[Maino]] was released on February 15, 2015. A music video for the song features Jayne dancing in an underground club with an entourage of dancers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/erika-jayne-crazy-music-video-1396677/|title=Erika Jayne Debuts Music Video For Crazy|work=|publisher=WetPaint |date= March 12, 2015|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref> Jayne released her new single \"[[How Many Fucks]]\" on April 19, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/erika-jayne-doesnt-give-a-f-in-her-latest-video-1740647648.html|title=Erika Jayne Doesn't Give a F*** in Her Latest Video|last=papermagazine|website=PAPERMAG|access-date=2016-04-30}}</ref> After its release, \"How Many Fucks\" received generally favorable reviews from contemporary [[Music journalism|music critics]]. In a highly positive review, Julia Brucculieri of ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' praised both the track and its corresponding video for being catchy and sexy.<ref name=\"The Huffington Post review\">{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/real-housewife-erika-jayne-music-video_us_57177e2ce4b0018f9cbbae4f|title=\u2018Real Housewife\u2019 Erika Jayne Gives Absolutely Zero F**ks In New Music Video|last1=Brucculieri|first1=Julia|date=April 20, 2016|accessdate=April 24, 2016|work=[[The Huffington Post]]}}</ref> Jordan Miller of ''BreatheHeavy'' gave the song a favorable review, saying the song is \"a blazing gay anthem.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.breatheheavy.com/housewives-star-erika-jaynes-new-song-is-lit/|title=Housewives Star Erika Jayne's New Song Is Lit - BreatheHeavy.com|website=breatheheavy.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-07}}</ref> Jayne was named the third \"Next Big Sound\" by [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'']] in early 2016.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/erika-jayne/chart-history/next-big-sound-25/song/966169|title=Erika Jayne Artist Chart Chart History|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-06-27}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, she joined the cast of ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]'' for the show's sixth season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/showtracker/la-et-st-erika-girardi-interview-20160308-story.html|title=A conversation with 'Real Housewives' star Erika Girardi, our latest reality TV obsession|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|website=latimes.com|access-date=2016-05-01}}</ref> She soon became a fan favorite on the show and her appearance was well-received by the public.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/738339/why-erika-girardi-is-our-new-favorite-on-the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills|title=Why Erika Girardi Is Our New Fave on RHOBH|website=E! Online|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-30}}</ref> In July 2016, she appeared as Tech Frances in the [[Science fiction film|science fiction]] [[television film]] ''[[Sharknado: The 4th Awakens]]''. In October 2016, Jayne appeared on the [[Animal Planet]] series ''[[Tanked]]'', in the episode \"[[Tanked#Season 11 (2016)|Real Aquariums of Beverly Hills]]\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=McLennan|first1=Cindy|title=Tanked: Animal Planet to Air 100th Episode in April|url=http://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/tanked-animal-planet-air-100th-episode-april/|website=TV Series Finale|accessdate=October 10, 2016|date=March 31, 2016}}</ref> In the episode, she requested an aquarium that has room for an octopus.<ref>{{cite web|title=Erika Girardi is Getting Tanked|url=http://www.animalplanet.com/tv-shows/tanked/videos/erika-girardi-is-getting-tanked/|website=Animal Planet|accessdate=October 10, 2016}}</ref> On November 7, 2016, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' broke news that Jayne would guest-star on the [[CBS]] daytime [[soap opera]] ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'', as Farrah Dubose, and would share scenes with her ''Real Housewives'' co-star, [[Eileen Davidson]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rice|first1=Lynette|title=''Real Housewives'' Stars to Reunite on ''Young and the Restless''|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/07/real-housewives-erica-jayne-eileen-davidson|accessdate=November 7, 2016|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=November 7, 2016|location=United States}}</ref>\n\n=== 2017\u20132018: Memoir and The Pretty Mess Tour ===\nJayne performed her new single \"[[Xxpensive|XXpen$ive]]\" for the first time on ''[[Watch What Happens Live with Andy Cohen]]'' on January 4, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-jayne-new-single-xxpensive-watch-what-happens-live-with-andy-cohen-performance-video|title=This Legendary Erika Jayne Performance Proves It's \"XXpen$ive\" to Be Her|date=2017-01-04|newspaper=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2017-02-15|language=en-US}}</ref> Music video for the single was officially released on February 15, 2017. She described the song as \"over-the-top, fabulous and fun.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/real-housewives-beverly-hills-erika-jaynes-xxpensive-music-video-full/|title=It\u2019s Here! See Erika Jayne\u2019s Over-the-Top \u2018XXPEN$IVE\u2019 Music Video: \u2018It\u2019s \u201980s Madonna All the Way Down\u2019|date=2017-02-15|newspaper=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2017-02-15|language=en-US}}</ref> Lyrically, it talks about [[materialism]] and entertainment. In May 2017, the song was featured on an episode of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' as [[Chris Pine]] and [[Bobby Moynihan]] held a [[lip sync]] battle to the song.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/chris-pine-impersonates-erika-jayne-on-snl|title=Chris Pine Channeled Erika Jayne's Dance Moves on SNL and Absolutely Killed It|date=2017-05-08|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2017-05-09|language=en-US}}</ref> On March 1, 2017, Jayne was revealed as one of the contestants who would compete on [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 24)|season 24]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''. She was paired with professional dancer [[Gleb Savchenko]] who had been previously partnered with Jayne's ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]'' co-star, [[Lisa Vanderpump]] when she competed in Season 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-2017-season-24-celebrity-cast-partners/story?id=45767534|title=\u2018Dancing With the Stars\u2019 2017: Season 24 celebrity cast and partners revealed on 'GMA\u2019|work=ABC News|access-date=March 1, 2017|date=March 1, 2017}}</ref> They were the fourth couple eliminated from the competition, finishing 9th place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/04/17/dwts-normani-kordei-tops-disney-week-erika-jayne-hangs-up-her-dancing-shoes/100587646/|title=\u2018Dancing With the Stars': Normani Kordei kills it, Erika Jayne exits|work=USA Today|access-date=April 25, 2017|date=April 17, 2017}}</ref> Jayne was hospitalized after she sustained a shoulder injury during her run on ''Dancing with the Stars''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-4546196/Erika-Jayne-undergoes-surgery-fix-secret-DWTS-injury.html|title=Erika Jayne undergoes surgery to fix secret DWTS injury|work=Mail Online|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/erika-jayne-hospitalized-rhobh-star-heads-into-surgery-for-secret-dancing-with-the-stars-injury/|title=Erika Jayne Hospitalized: RHOBH Star Heads into Surgery for Secret Dancing with the Stars Injury|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en}}</ref> She had a surgical procedure for an upper body tear in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0149633/bio|title=Erika Jayne|website=IMDb|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref> In July 2017, Jayne announced her partnership with make up brand ''BeautyBlender.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BWQDbqGhFnU/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"SURPRISE! My first beauty partnership with my all-time favorite brand @beautyblender!! Who else is obsessed with this swirl blender?\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2018-07-04}}</ref> \"The Beautyblender Swirl\" starring Erika Jayne became available at [[Sephora]] on July 8, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allure.com/story/beautyblender-swirl-luanch|title=Beautyblender Is Dropping a New Marbelized Shade and We're OBSESSED|last=Abelman|first=Devon|work=Allure|access-date=2017-07-08|language=en}}</ref> The following August, it was announced by media outlets, that she is collaborating with ''Too Faced Cosmetics'', potentially on new products.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/too-faced-erika-jayne-real-housewives|title=Brace Yourselves: A Too Faced x Erika Jayne Collab Is Coming|last=Nussbaum|first=Rachel|work=Glamour|access-date=2017-08-27|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elle.com/beauty/makeup-skin-care/news/a47310/erika-jayne-too-faced-makeup/|title=Real Housewives Star Erika Jayne Teases a Makeup Collection|date=2017-08-10|work=ELLE|access-date=2017-08-27|language=en}}</ref> She starred in ''Too Faced''<nowiki/>'s \"Better Than Sex Mascara\" campaign in late 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elle.com/beauty/a12274698/too-faced-partners-with-erika-jayne/?src=socialflowTW|title=Erika Jayne Joins Forces With Too Faced|date=2017-10-04|work=ELLE|access-date=2017-10-08|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/stylish/news/rhobhs-erika-jayne-partners-with-too-faceds-better-than-sex-w507534|title=Erika Jayne Is Starring in Too Faced\u2019s Sex Campaign|work=Us Weekly|access-date=2017-10-08}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=toofacedcosmetics|title=Too Faced Better Than Sex Mascara \u2013 Starring Erika Jayne|date=2017-10-19|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLJJU92FoHs|accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, she appeared in a [[Christina Aguilera]]-themed episode on ''[[Lip Sync Battle]]'' competing against [[Taye Diggs]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-5313061/Erika-Jayne-sings-Fighter-Christina-Aguilera.html|title=Erika Jayne sings Fighter in front of Christina Aguilera|work=Mail Online|access-date=2018-03-03}}</ref> She performed Aguilera's famous hits \"[[Fighter (Christina Aguilera song)|Fighter]]\" and \"[[Genie in a Bottle|Genie In a Bottle]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://etcanada.com/news/292875/sneak-peek-christina-aguilera-watches-erika-jayne-perform-fighter-on-xtina-themed-lip-sync-battle/|title=Sneak Peek: Christina Aguilera Watches Erika Jayne Perform \u2018Fighter\u2019 On Xtina-Themed \u2018Lip Sync Battle\u2019|last=Furdyk|first=Brent|date=2018-01-24|work=ET Canada|access-date=2018-03-03}}</ref> She has also previously performed at Aguilera's 36th birthday party in December 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/pictures/inside-christina-aguileras-36th-birthday-party-w455464/jumpin-jumpin-w455474/|title=Inside Christina Aguilera\u2019s 36th Birthday Party|date=2016-12-16|work=Us Weekly|access-date=2018-03-03|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/kylie-jenner-christina-aguilera-birthday-party-photos/|title=Kylie Jenner Attends Christina Aguilera's Birthday Bash Dressed as Vintage Xtina|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-03-03|language=en}}</ref> On March 5, 2018, she appeared as a guest co-host on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]]'s ''[[Dish Nation]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dishnation.com/erika-jayne-spills-pretty-mess-tea-new-book/|title=ERIKA JAYNE SPILLS A 'PRETTY MESS' OF HER OWN TEA IN NEW BOOK - Dish Nation {{!}} Entertaining Entertainment News|date=2018-03-06|work=Dish Nation {{!}} Entertaining Entertainment News|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dishnation.com/real-housewives-erika-jayne-oscar-fashion/|title=ERIKA JAYNE'S 'REAL' TAKE ON ALL THE OSCAR FASHION - Dish Nation {{!}} Entertaining Entertainment News|date=2018-03-05|work=Dish Nation {{!}} Entertaining Entertainment News|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en-US}}</ref> In early 2018 she released a memoir with Brian Moylan, ''Pretty Mess'', with color photos and personal stories.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-4707362/Erika-Jayne-talks-new-book-Pretty-Mess.html|title=Erika Jayne talks new book Pretty Mess|work=Mail Online|access-date=2017-07-21}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/tv/real-housewives-beverly-hills-erika-girardi-erika-jayne-pretty-mess-memoir-exclusive/|title=RHOBH's Erika Jayne Is 'Fun, Fearless and Here to Tell All' in Upcoming Memoir Pretty Mess|date=2017-07-18|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2017-07-21|language=en-US}}</ref> \u201cI hope my intimate story can inspire readers to become their own strong, confident and vibrant pretty messes,\" she said in the book's press release.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-girardi-memoir|title=Erika Girardi Is Clearly Plotting World Domination by Announcing Her Next Project|date=2017-07-18|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=July 21, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://pagesix.com/2017/07/18/rhobh-star-erika-girardi-penning-memoir/|title=\u2018RHOBH\u2019 star Erika Girardi penning memoir|last=Hendricks|first=Jaclyn|date=July 18, 2017|website=Page Six|access-date=2017-07-21}}</ref> The book was ninth on the [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The'' ''New York Times'' Best Seller list]] and fifth on the Publishers Weekly Bestseller List.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/ap/article-5560255/PUBLISHERS-WEEKLY-BEST-SELLERS.html|title=PUBLISHERS WEEKLY BEST-SELLERS|work=Mail Online|access-date=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2018/04/07/combined-print-and-e-book-nonfiction/|title=NEW YORK TIMES COMBINED PRINT AND E-BOOK NONFICTION BEST-SELLERS|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> In March 2018, she appeared in a [[Vogue (magazine)|''Vogue'']]-feature and a short film after spending one day working for the fashion magazine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/923142/watch-erika-jayne-spend-a-day-working-at-vogue|title=Watch Erika Jayne Spend a Day Working at Vogue|work=E! Online|access-date=2018-05-10|language=en-US}}</ref> Her single, \"Cars\" was released on April 10, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.etonline.com/inside-erika-jaynes-ultra-glam-pretty-mess-clubhouse-exclusive-99511|title=Inside Erika Jayne\u2019s Ultra-Glam, \u2018Pretty Mess\u2019 Clubhouse (Exclusive)|work=Entertainment Tonight|access-date=2018-04-04|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-jaynes-new-single-cars-itunes-pre-sale|title=Erika Jayne Has a New Single Coming Out and Your Life Is About to be Forever Changed|date=2018-04-03|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-04-04|language=en-US}}</ref> The song interpolates the chorus of [[L'Trimm]]'s famous single \"[[Cars With the Boom]]\" (1988).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8301673/erika-jayne-pretty-mess-interview|title=Erika Jayne on Her Friendship With Christina Aguilera & Lifelong Love for Dolly Parton|website=Billboard|access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref> Upon its release, \"Cars\" has received mostly favorable reception from music critics, who noted the song as significantly different from her previous releases.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://champagneandshade.com/2018/04/14/erika-jayne-new-song-forgiven/|title=Erika Jayne\u2019s new song reveals people have forgiven her|date=2018-04-14|work=Champagne and Shade|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en-US}}</ref> Despite the song's popularity among fans, \"Cars\" still did not manage to make an impact on the charts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://champagneandshade.com/2018/04/14/erika-jayne-new-song-forgiven/|title=Erika Jayne\u2019s new song reveals people have forgiven her|date=2018-04-14|work=Champagne and Shade|access-date=2018-07-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" />\n\nIn May 2018, it was announced that she would reprise her role as real estate agent Farrah Dubose on ''The Young and the Restless'' for a two-episode guest stint.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bricker|first=Tierney|title=Erika Girardi Is Returning to ''The Young and the Restless''!|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/931519/get-ready-genoa-city-erika-girardi-is-returning-to-the-young-and-the-restless-in-a-major-way|website=[[E! Online]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|accessdate=May 2, 2018|location=United States|date=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-girardi-returns-to-the-young-and-the-restless-details-video|title=Will Erika Girardi's Return to the Young & the Restless Take a Sexy Turn?|date=2017-04-21|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-05-25|language=en-US}}</ref> After media speculation, Girardi confirmed she is returning for the ninth season of ''The Real Housewives'' ''of Beverly Hills''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lifeandstylemag.com/posts/erika-jayne-leaving-rhobh-159696|title=Erika Jayne Sparks Rumors That She's Leaving 'Real Housewives of Beverly Hills'|date=2018-05-09|work=Life & Style|access-date=2018-07-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-5746449/Erika-Jayne-ravishing-red-View-confirms-NOT-leaving-RHOBH.html|title=Erika Jayne as she confirms she is NOT leaving RHOBH on The View|work=Mail Online|access-date=2018-05-19}}</ref> Jessi Roti of ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' wrote in late 2018 that \"Jayne has become one of top reasons to tune in every week. Not just for the drama, but for the authenticity she added to the high gloss of the show with her fast-and-hard truths and keen self-awareness, and to catch a glimpse at what\u2019s next for the performer, who was already established in the world of dance music.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://eu.detroitnews.com/story/entertainment/music/2018/10/23/tv-bravo-real-housewives-beverly-hills-erika-jayne-singer-billboard-chart-club-music/38252769/|title=\u2018Real Housewives\u2019 star Erika Jayne lives out loud|work=Detroit News|access-date=2018-10-24|language=en}}</ref> She hosted the [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard Music Awards Red Carpet Live'']] alongside AJ Gibson on May 20, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8456667/billboard-music-awards-2018-red-carpet-pre-show|title=Billboard Music Awards 2018: Hosts Announced For Official Red Carpet Pre-Show|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-5751293/Billboards-2018-Erika-Jayne-puts-legs-display-mini.html|title=Billboards 2018: Erika Jayne puts her legs on display in a mini|work=Mail Online|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref> The following August, she announced her collaboration with [[ShoeDazzle]], an online shoe and accessories website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BmMTfPyA3iq/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"Coming soon... \ud83d\udc60\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2018-08-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/lookbook/erika-girardi-teased-shoe-collaboration-with-shoedazzle|title=Erika Girardi Just Teased a New Fashion Collab and We\u2019re Freaking Out|last=|first=|date=2018-08-08|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-08-09|language=en-US}}</ref> ShoeDazzle's commercial campaign features Jayne and her single \"[[Xxpensive|Xxpen$ive]]\".<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/style/erika-girardi-shoedazzle-commercial/|title=Get RHOBH Star Erika Girardi's Signature Style Thanks to Her New Partnership with ShoeDazzle|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-09-04|language=en}}</ref> She teamed up with ShoeDazzle as their latest \u201c[[Muses|muse]]\u201d and shared her 14 must-have favorite shoe styles for fall 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.shoedazzle.com/index.cfm?action=catalog.shop_influencer&influencer=erika_jayne&bp=0&code=C86B3C&irad=429467&irmp=1289912|title=Influencer {{!}} ShoeDazzle|website=ShoeDazzle|access-date=2018-09-04}}</ref> Customers will get to see her favorite shoe styles with a new collection each month.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/erika-jayne-steps-into-new-role-as-shoedazzle-muse-300705638.html|title=Erika Jayne Steps Into New Role As ShoeDazzle Muse|website=prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2018-09-04}}</ref> \"I\u2019ve been looking for the perfect partner to help me invite my fans to step into my closet, and my collaboration with ShoeDazzle affords my fans the chance to do just that,\" Jayne said in the press release.<ref name=\":9\" /> She also announced her plans to design her own line for the brand in 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://pagesix.com/2018/09/04/rhobh-erika-girardi-designing-low-priced-shoe-line/|title=RHOBH Erika Girardi designing low-priced shoe line|date=2018-09-04|work=Page Six|access-date=2018-09-04|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2018, she was a featured speaker at [[TED (conference)|TedxPasadena]] and gave a [[TED (conference)|TED]] speech on transforming the future and putting words to action.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tedxpasadena.org/transform2018/|title=TRANSFORM 2018 - TEDxPasadena|website=tedxpasadena.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/erika-jayne-to-speak-at-ted-talk-tedxpasadena-on-pretty-mess|title=Erika Jayne Is Ready to Bring Her Pretty Mess to a TED Talk|date=2018-09-17|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-09-20|language=en-US}}</ref> Her speech was titled \"My Unapologetic Alter Ego: Living Life as an Exaggerated Figment of People's Imaginations\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/TEDxPasadena/status/1043655013141082113|title=TEDxPasadena on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-09-23|language=en}}</ref>  She made a guest appearance on an episode of [[BET]]'s sports drama television series ''[[Hit the Floor (TV series)|Hit the Floor]],'' in the episode \"Hot Streak.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/hit-the-floor-bet-cancelled-renewed-season-five/|title=Hit the Floor on BET: Cancelled or Season 5? (Release Date) - canceled TV shows - TV Series Finale|date=2018-08-08|work=canceled TV shows - TV Series Finale|access-date=2018-08-14|language=en-US}}</ref> She portrayed a [[media mogul]] called Beverly.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BmeHhJ_BLPU/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"Tonight #hitthefloor on @BET \" Beverly \" is going to make an interesting offer.\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2018-08-14}}</ref> In 2018, Erika Jayne appeared on various television shows to promote her music and book, including ''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]'', ''[[The Wendy Williams Show]]'', ''[[Larry King Now]]'', ''[[Megyn Kelly Today]]''''',''' ''[[Steve (talk show)|Steve]]'' and ''Kandi Koated Nights''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/tv/kandi-burruss-kandi-koated-nights-talk-show/|title=RHOA Star Kandi Burruss Is Bringing Her 'Sexy Talk Show' Kandi Koated Nights to Bravo|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/kandi-koated-nights/personal-space/erika-jayne-picked-her-two-most-important-qualities-in-a-man|title=Erika Jayne Made Her Dream Man ... With the Help of Kandi Burruss?!|date=2018-07-06|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en-US}}</ref> In September 2018, she was as a guest editor for [[Fashion week|Fashion Week]] at [[E!]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/966233/erika-jayne-shares-4-fall-style-trends-that-scream-s-e-x|title=Erika Jayne Shares 4 Fall Style Trends That Scream S-E-X|last=|first=|date=2018-09-07|work=E! Online|access-date=2018-09-07|language=en-US}}</ref> In late 2018, she will produce a series of concerts at several venues, titled [[Erika Jayne Presents: The Pretty Mess Tour]].<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://fullscreenlive.com/event/erika-jayne/|title=Erika Jayne - Fullscreen Live|website=fullscreenlive.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref> The concert tour begins on September 28 and ends on December 21, 2018.<ref name=\":8\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/erikajayne?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor|title=Erika Jayne (@erikajayne) {{!}} Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref> In October 2018, Jayne performed her single  \"Xxpen$ive\" on ''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]'' in honor of her friend [[Meghan McCain]]'s birthday.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Culture/meghan-mccain-surprise-birthday-gift-andy-cohen-view/story?id=58686757|title=Meghan McCain gets surprise birthday gift from Andy Cohen on 'The View'|last=News|first=A. B. C.|date=2018-10-23|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2018-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=The View|title=Erika Jayne performs her hit song 'XXpen$ive'|date=2018-10-23|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kr8I6GBv14Y|access-date=2018-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/erikajayne/status/1054799592057982976|title=Erika Jayne on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-10-24|language=en}}</ref> Michael Love Michael of ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' magazine wrote that Jayne was \"wearing a sparkling leotard situation that we could just as easily picture on [[Britney Spears]] during her [[Britney Spears: Piece of Me Tour|Piece of Me]] residency.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.papermag.com/erika-jayne-the-view-2614639379.html|title=Erika Jayne Gave a Pop Extravaganza on 'The View'|date=2018-10-23|work=PAPER|access-date=2018-10-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019\u2013present: Beauty collaborations and Broadway ===\nShe designed a makeup collection for Too Faced Cosmetics, released on February 12, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/lookbook/erika-girardi-x-too-faced-cosmetics-first-look|title=Erika Girardi Shares a Peek at Her New Makeup Line, And We're So Excited (UPDATE)|date=2019-01-25|website=Bravo TV Official Site|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allure.com/story/erika-jayne-for-too-faced-collaboration-sneak-peek|title=Too Faced Is Teaming Up With This Real Housewife For Its New Collab|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Allure|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> The collection consisted of a 12-shade eye shadow palette, a body shimmer, a highlighter, two color and gloss lip kits, and a lip plumper.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hellogiggles.com/beauty/makeup/erika-jayne-too-faced-interview/|title=Erika Jayne talks to us about working with Too Faced on her Pretty Mess makeup collection|website=HelloGiggles|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/beauty-features/erika-jayne-jerrod-blandino-too-faced-collab-1202991657/|title=\u2018We Just Had a Baby\u2019: Erika Jayne, Jerrod Blandino on Too Faced Collab|last=Tietjen|first=Alexa|last2=Tietjen|first2=Alexa|date=2019-01-30|website=WWD|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> In March 2019, she launched a shoe collection for [[ShoeDazzle]], divided into two collections titled Erika Girardi and Erika Jayne.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footwearnews.com/2019/fashion/collaborations/shoe-dazzle-erika-jayne-collection-release-info-1202758227/|title=\u2018Real Housewives of Beverly Hills\u2019 Star Erika Jayne\u2019s ShoeDazzle Collab Has Dual Naughty and Nice Collections|last=Miller|first=Claudia|last2=Miller|first2=Claudia|date=2019-03-06|website=Footwear News|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fashionista.com/2019/03/erika-jayne-shoedazzle-collaboration-collection|title=Erika Jayne Thinks We Should All be Mowing the Lawn in 5-Inch Pumps|last=McCall|first=Tyler|website=Fashionista|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> Jayne released a second shoe collection for ShoeDazzle on September 6, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/erika-jayne-shoedazzle-fall-collection-1203255214/|title=Erika Jayne Partners With ShoeDazzle on Fall Collection|last=Tietjen|first=Alexa|last2=Tietjen|first2=Alexa|date=2019-09-05|website=WWD|language=en|access-date=2019-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/lookbook/erika-girardi-reveals-fall-2019-shoedazzle-collab|title=Erika Girardi's New Shoe Collection Includes (Gasp!) Flats|date=2019-09-06|website=Bravo TV Official Site|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref> Jayne was featured on rapper [[Brooke Candy]]'s new single titled \"Drip\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gagadaily.com/forums/topic/302694-brooke-candy-announces-2nd-single-drip-live-performance/|title=Brooke Candy Announces 2nd Single 'Drip' + Live Performance|website=Gaga Daily|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref> The pair performed \"Drip\" at the VFiles fashion show at [[New York Fashion Week]]. ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' magazine described the single as \"is an in-your-face femme power anthem that combines both stars' styles into a singular, sweat-slicked bop. It's a little of vintage Brooke Candy attitude, a little Erika Jayne-branded bondage, and a whole lot of sex appeal.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/erika-jayne-brooke-candy-vfiles-2640232823.html|title=Erika Jayne and Brooke Candy Performed at NYFW Together|last=Wetmore|first=Brendan|date=|website=Paper|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In September 2019, she walked the runway for [[Kyle Richards]]' and Shahida Clayton's new women's clothing brand at New York Fashion Week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/lisa-rinna-erika-jayne-more-020052593.html|title=Lisa Rinna, Erika Jayne & More 'RHOBH' Cast Members Walk in Kyle Richards' First Fashion Show (Exclusive)|website=yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heraldpublicist.com/lisa-rinna-dorit-kemsley-more-real-housewives-strut-their-stuff-in-kyle-richards-nyfw-show/|title=Lisa Rinna, Dorit Kemsley & More 'Real Housewives' Strut Their Stuff In Kyle Richards' NYFW Show|last=snehith|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref>\n\nOn September 25, 2019, Erika Jayne announced that she is playing [[Roxie Hart]] in the musical ''[[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]]'' on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ChicagoMusical/status/1176877794346897409|title=It'd be criminal to miss @erikajayne as Roxie Hart. Catch her on Broadway beginning January 6.pic.twitter.com/RKt7TAyZ1D|last=Musical|first=Chicago The|date=2019-09-25|website=@ChicagoMusical|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2019/09/25/rhobh-star-erika-jayne-to-make-broadway-debut-in-chicago/|title=\u2018RHOBH\u2019 star Erika Jayne to make Broadway debut in \u2018Chicago\u2019|last=Bailey-Millado|first=Rob|date=2019-09-25|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> Her performances were originally set to run from January 6 to March 29, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/theater/rhobh-erika-jayne-chicago-the-musical-roxie-hart/|title=From Beverly Hills to Broadway! RHOBH's Erika Jayne to Play Roxie Hart in Chicago the Musical|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/erika-jayne-chicago-2640620336.html|title=Erika Jayne Is Making Her Broadway Debut|date=2019-09-26|website=PAPER|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref name=\":11\" /> On March 12, 2020, she announced that her Broadway production has ended weeks early due to [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Coronavirus]] shutdown.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/broadway-stars-react-theater-shutdowns-232443181.html|title=Broadway Stars React To Theater Shutdowns With Well Wishes & Good Humor: \"Welp, It\u2019s Been Real Y\u2019all\" Tweets David Alan Grier|website=yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> [[Governor of New York|New York Governor]] [[Andrew Cuomo]] and Broadway League President Charlotte St. Martin announced that all Broadway performances have been canceled until April 12, 2020 due to concerns about the Coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/theater/erika-jayne-forced-to-end-her-broadway-chicago-run-weeks-early-due-to-coronavirus-shutdown/|title=Erika Jayne Forced to End Her Broadway Chicago Run Weeks Early Due to Coronavirus Shutdown|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==Public image==\nFashion has also been a part of Jayne's music career and image.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/lookbook/erika-girardi-sheer-jumpsuit-for-cr-fashion-book|title=Erika Girardi Can Work a See-Through Bodysuit Like No Other|date=2018-04-13|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref> She has frequently worn clothes designed by [[Gucci]], [[Moschino]], [[Versace]], [[Balmain (fashion house)|Balmain]], and [[Alexander McQueen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bigblondehair.com/character/erika-girardi/|title=Erika GIrardi {{!}} You Source for Real Housewives Fashion and Style|website=bigblondehair.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.brit.co/erika-jayne-beauty-hair-wardrobe-costs/|title=Erika Jayne Spends $40,000 Each Month on Her Glam Look|access-date=2018-06-23|language=en-us}}</ref> Tyler McCall of Fashionista.com called her \"debatably the most stylish cast member of any ''Real Housewives'' franchise.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://fashionista.com/2017/04/erika-jayne-real-housewives-style-clothes|title=Erika Jayne: How I Shop|work=Fashionista|access-date=2018-06-23|language=en}}</ref> In 2018, she was the first star of ''[[The Real Housewives]]'' media franchise to attend the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America|CFDA Fashion Awards]] and was placed on several \"best-dressed lists\" after her appearance on the award show''.''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/style/cfda-awards-2018-erika-jayne-suit/?xid=socialflow_twitter_peoplemag|title=Erika Jayne Is the 'First Housewife' to Ever Attend the CFDA Awards: See Her 'Sophistica