PIN\u2019 IT REAL|date=2016-10-31|work=Pasadena Magazine|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cvlux.com/fashion-beauty-1/2017/11/5/naughty-but-nice|title=Naughty But Nice|work=CVLUX|access-date=2017-12-30|language=en-US}}</ref> Jayne names [[Rita Hayworth]] and [[Marilyn Monroe]] as her style icons. She has also discussed how her mother and grandmother have been a continuing inspiration to her.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vogue.com/article/erika-girardi-jayne-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-bella-gigi-hadid-tom-ford-celebrity-style|title=The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills\u2019s Erika Jayne on Her Style Inspiration, Bella and Gigi Hadid, and Vintage Alexander McQueen|newspaper=Vogue|access-date=2017-02-22|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, ''[[Forbes]]''<nowiki/>' Seamus Kirst wrote an article about how being on ''The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills'' has benefitted Jayne's music career.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/seamuskirst/2016/02/22/erikajayne/#7c36795bc7fe|title='The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills' Cast Mate [sic&#93; Erika Girardi On The Business Of Being Erika Jayne|last=Kirst|first=Seamus|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-10-31|language=en}}</ref> Since joining the show'','' Jayne said she has gained nearly 200,000 more [[Instagram]] followers and over 30,000 more followers on [[Twitter]]. Kirst stated that \"this rise in visibility on social media is financially lucrative for the performing artist. Jayne is popular on social media and endorses products such as beauty and wellness products on [[Instagram]]. She has partnered with several brands, including ''FabFitFun'' beauty subscription box, ''[[Ketel One]]'' liquor,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bvk-gGjA3W1/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"#ad Raising a glass with @KetelOne_US to celebrate thirty years of the GLAAD Media Awards shining a light on progress and accelerating\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> ''Teami Blends'' teas,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BsKCOqRAfBX/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"It takes a lot of work to be this fab\ud83d\udc8bbut traveling so much for my tour has been HARSH on my body, I felt bloated and held onto some weight\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> ''Svedka Vodka'' liquor,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BVWf0ZgBOxY/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"@svedkavodka new blue raspberry flavor is my new \" One Hot Pleasure \" #studiosvedka #sponsor\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> ''DIFF Eyewear'' sunglasses<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BS1ijkkB7Os/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"Paying it forward. \ud83d\udd76\ufe0f DIFF donates a pair of reading glasses for every pair of sunglasses sold Use code PRETTYMESS for 25% off at\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> and ''Freixenet'' wine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BpYcOPMAJLY/|title=Erika Jayne on Instagram: \"On my way to @freixenetusa Black Magic Halloween Party!! Check my stories for an exclusive look inside the event. \ud83d\ude3d #FXCava #DarkandBubbly\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref>\n\nJayne was [[Parody|parodied]] in the \"New Wife\" sketch by [[Cecily Strong]] on the late-night show ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' aired on November 4, 2017.<ref>{{Citation|last=Saturday Night Live|title=New Wife - SNL|date=2017-11-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OCxx2jFu1rI|accessdate=2018-06-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/did-saturday-night-live-serve-up-some-erika-jayne-fierceness|title=Did Saturday Night Live Serve Up Some Erika Jayne Fierceness?|date=2017-11-06|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-06-12|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/901368/erika-jayne-is-ready-to-meet-her-saturday-night-live-alter-ego-call-me-candace|title=Erika Jayne Is Ready to Meet Her SNL Alter Ego|work=E! Online|access-date=2018-06-12|language=en-US}}</ref> In December 2017, [[Kim Kardashian]]'s mobile game, ''[[Kim Kardashian: Hollywood]]'' added Jayne as a new virtual character as a part of a special quest for players.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://popculture.com/reality-tv/2017/12/05/rhobh-erika-jayne-kim-kardashian-hollywood/|title='RHOBH' Cast Member Erika Jayne Joins 'Kim Kardashian: Hollywood' Mobile Game|website=Reality TV|language=en|access-date=2017-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://fuzzable.com/real-housewives-beverly-hills-erika-jayne-joins-kim-kardashian-hollywood/|title=Real Housewives of Beverly Hills\u2019 Erika Jayne Joins Kim Kardashian: Hollywood|date=2017-12-05|work=Fuzzable|access-date=2017-12-06|language=en-US}}</ref> Players who pass the seventh level of the game can now choose to become Erika Jayne and perform a club hit in one of her outfits. \"It's surreal.There I am, little Erika Jayne, walking and talking. It's incredible and I'm very thankful, so thank you, Kim,\" Jayne told ''The Daily Dish''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/kim-kardashian-just-made-erika-jayne-a-fierce-character-in-her-app-game|title=Kim Kardashian Just Made Erika Jayne a Fierce Character in Her App Game|date=2017-12-21|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2017, she also began co-hosting various television programs, including red carpet awards show coverages and specials.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://okmagazine.com/photos/2018-billboard-music-award-red-carpet-arrivals-photos/|title=2018 Billboard Music Awards Red Carpet: See What Stars Made It To The Big Night!|date=2018-05-20|work=OK! Magazine|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n<nowiki/>{{Quote box\n| width = 300px\n| align = left\n| quote = \"I remember being in those clubs and there would always be that one song that would make you want to toss your drink to the side and run out and dance your heart out. And I realized instantly that those were the kinds of records I wanted to make. I was heavily influenced by Madonna and wanted to convey that same feeling.\"\n|source=\u2014Girardi, on her influences<ref>[https://303magazine.com/2013/09/reel-deal-erika-jayne-qa/ The Reel Deal: Erika Jayne Q&A] September 9, 2013</ref>\n}}\n\n''[[The New York Post]]'' called her \"the self-proclaimed [[showgirl]] of ''The'' ''Real Housewives of Beverly Hills''.\"<ref name=\":18\" /> She created an [[alter ego]], \"Erika Jayne\" when performing on stage.<ref>[http://chicago.gopride.com/news/interview.cfm/articleid/714100 Erika Jayne Interview] Chicago Go Pride. Retrieved January 29, 2016</ref> She has described her alter ego by saying: \"Erika Jayne is 100 percent me. She\u2019s obviously a stage persona \u2014 a larger-than-life, over-the-top stage persona \u2014 but she\u2019s still, at her heart, me. I think there\u2019s a little bit of a showman in all of us, and it\u2019s just a matter of whether or not you bring that out of yourself or allow it to show itself.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/erika-jayne-pop-star_us_5aec942fe4b0c4f1932250a3|title=Erika Jayne Reveals The Musical Moments That Changed Her Life|last=Michelson|first=Noah|date=2018-05-08|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> Jayne's stage performances and travels have also been created into a book by photographer Marco Bollinger.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.brigitte.la/work/erika-jayne/|title=BRIGITTE LA \u203a Erika Jayne|website=BRIGITTE LA|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theyellowloft.squarespace.com/erika-jayne/|title=Erika Jayne|website=The Yellow Loft|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> Jayne has received praise for her stage presence and routines during live performances.<ref>[http://www.sheknows.com/entertainment/articles/1092131/things-to-know-about-erika-jayne-real-housewives-beverly-hills 5 Things to Know About Erika Jayne] She Knows. January 29, 2016</ref> Following her appearance on [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|''Dancing with the Stars'']], Girardi was the center of criticism for being too risque.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inquisitr.com/4134864/erika-jayne-says-shell-never-tone-it-down-after-critics-say-she-is-too-sexy-on-dancing-with-the-stars/|title=Erika Jayne Says She\u2019ll Never Tone It Down After Critics Say She Is \u2018Too Sexy\u2019 On \u2018Dancing With The Stars\u2019|date=2017-04-10|work=The Inquisitr|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en-US}}</ref> \"I know the salsa's sort of a sexy type of dance. For me, it was a little bit too raunchy, but I'm what I am,\" ''Dancing with the Stars'' judge [[Len Goodman]] told Girardi. Other judges, including [[Julianne Hough]] praised the performance, saying it was a good thing for Erika to encourage women to see themselves as sexual beings.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.refinery29.com/2017/03/146372/erika-jayne-dancing-with-the-stars?bucketed=true&bucketing_referrer=https://www.google.fi/|title=Was Erika Jayne Slut Shamed On \"DWTS\"? Twitter Thinks So|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en}}</ref> \"I felt [the critiques] were more personal than it was technical,\" Girardi later said on [[Jenny McCarthy]]'s [[SiriusXM]] show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/922220/erika-jayne-s-5-biggest-confessions-from-her-truthful-chat-with-jenny-mccarthy|title=5 Biggest Confessions From Erika Jayne's Chat With Jenny McCarthy|work=E! Online|access-date=2018-05-02|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nJayne supports the [[LGBT community|LGBTQ community]]. She was named  \"News Ally Entertainer of 2015\" at the LGBT Ally Awards in recognition of her ongoing support for the rights and equality of LGBTQ people around the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/media/2015/01/22/allred-jayne-receive-lgbt-ally-awards-thursday-night-la|title=Allred, Jayne to Receive LGBT Ally Awards Thursday Night in L.A.|date=2015-01-22|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manhattandigest.com/2016/09/06/one-on-one-with-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-erika-jayne/|title=One on One with Real Housewives of Beverly Hills\u2019 Erika Jayne!|date=2016-09-06|work=Manhattan Digest|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en-US}}</ref> She often performs at LGBTQ events and festivals, including [[pride parade]]s in [[Los Angeles]], [[San Francisco]], [[Dallas]], [[Toronto]], [[New York City|New York]] and [[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.songkick.com/artists/227099-erika-jayne/gigography|title=Erika Jayne Gigography, Tour History & Past Concerts \u2013 Songkick|language=en|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref> In 2017, she was the headliner for the 28th Annual [[GLAAD Media Award]]s after-party.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/213666_erika_jayne_to_headline_hyundai_s_28th_annual_glaad_media_awards_after_party|title=EXCLUSIVE: Erika Jayne to Headline Hyundai's 28th Annual GLAAD Media Awards After Party|work=Entertainment Tonight|access-date=2018-04-12|language=en}}</ref> Jayne was the host of \"Pride Month Conversation\" with author [[Ross Mathews]] on June 28, 2017 in California.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://laguestlist.com/event/living-best-life-erika-jayne-ross-mathews/|title=\"Living Your Best Life\" With Erika Jayne and Ross Mathews - LA Guestlist|work=LA Guestlist|access-date=2018-10-27|language=en-US}}</ref> In June 2018, [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] published her \"love letter\" to the LGBTQ community in celebration of the [[Pride Month]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/real-housewives-star-erika-jaynes-letter-to-the-lgbtq-community-shows-so-much-love-for-her-fans-9275987|title='Real Housewives' Fans Need To Read Erika Jayne's Amazing Letter To The LGBTQ+ Community|last=Witter|first=Brad|work=Bustle|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inquisitr.com/4926538/real-housewife-erika-jayne-pens-love-letter-to-lgbtq-community/|title=Real Housewife Erika Jayne Pens \u2018Love Letter\u2019 To LGBTQ Community|date=2018-06-04|work=The Inquisitr|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> In the letter she thanked the community for coming to her concerts, supporting her television career and making her feel free and empowered.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8458946/erika-jayne-love-letter-lgbtq-community-pride-month|title=Erika Jayne: Love Letter to the LGBTQ Community|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-ca/entertainment/music/news/erika-jayne-love-letter-to-the-lgbtq-community/ar-AAy8MCt|title=Erika Jayne: Love Letter to the LGBTQ Community|website=msn.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref>\n\n== Philanthropy ==\nGirardi and her husband are philanthropists and together they contribute to their community with frequent charitable donations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latlc.org/Honorary-Board/Tom-Girardi.shtml|title=Tom Girardi {{!}} Los Angeles Trial Lawyers' Charities {{!}}|website=Scott J. Corwin|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref>  In 2015, she participated in protest march against the [[Lychee and Dog Meat Festival|Yulin Dog Meat Festival]], where hundreds of supporters marched towards the Chinese Consulate. The protest march was organized by her ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]'' co-star [[Lisa Vanderpump]] and Girardi described the march as her \"favorite charity event.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://hauteliving.com/2015/12/rhobh-star-erika-jayne-haute-secrets/596671/|title=RHOBH Star Erika Jayne's Haute Secrets|date=2015-12-17|work=Haute Living|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en-US}}</ref> She participated in a fundraiser for [[Habitat for Humanity]] via a [[SoulCycle]] class hosted by Mauricio Umansky's real estate firm The Agency in 2016. She described the event by saying: \"It was a great way to stay fit and raise money for a good cause. I\u2019m glad it was a success. I would do it again anytime.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/season-6/blogs/erika-girardi/erika-girardi-even-erika-jayne|title=Erika Girardi: Even Erika Jayne Blushed!|date=2016-02-24|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-07-07|language=en-US}}</ref> She has worked in a project with Giveback Homes and Habitat for Humanity to help paint houses.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/season-6/blogs/erika-girardi/erika-girardi-kathryn-embarrassed|title=Erika Girardi: Kathryn Embarrassed Herself|date=2016-03-10|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-07-07|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2017, she volunteered at non-profit organization [[Project Angel Food]] and participated in [[Camille Grammer]]'s Perfume for Cancer fundraiser.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/03/rhobh-recap-season-8-episode-22.html|title=The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills Recap: Beverly Beaches|last=Moylan|first=Brian|work=Vulture|access-date=2018-09-15|language=en}}</ref> Girardi participated in an event geared towards female empowerment called \"Girl Cult Festival\" in [[Los Angeles]] on August 20, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tv.galoremag.com/video/girl-cult-festival-aug-20th-featuring-tyra-banks-willow-smith-erika-jayne-and-more|title=http://tv.galoremag.com/video/girl-cult-festival-aug-20th-featuring-tyra-banks-willow-smith-erika-jayne-and-more|website=tv.galoremag.com|access-date=2018-09-30}}</ref> She was a motivational speaker at the event and shared tips for becoming successful.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bigblondehair.com/erika-girardis-forgive-me-denim-jacket/|title=Erika Girardi\u2019s Forgive Me Denim Jacket {{!}} Big Blonde Hair|website=bigblondehair.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-30}}</ref>\n\nGirardi hosted the third annual \"Run to Remember \u2014 Los Angeles\" in honor of fallen police officers and first responders at [[The Grove at Farmers Market|The Grove]] on April 8, 2018. The event raised funds to serve families of those who have fallen, as well as supporting a variety of community programs such as police mentorships, education and scholarships for youth, equipment for local police and fire departments, at-risk-youth programs and veteran support.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.runtorememberla.org/|title=Home|website=Run To Remember LA|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-10}}</ref> In October 2018, Girardi sold 16 different items from her wardrobe on [[eBay]], including dresses seen on ''The'' ''Real Housewives of Beverly Hills'', [[Billboard Music Award]]s and [[Grammy Award]]s.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/lookbook/shop-erika-girardi-closet-on-ebay|title=You Can Shop Erika Girardi's Closet on eBay Right Now \u2014 and This Sale Includes Her Reunion Dress!|date=2018-10-03|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-10-04|language=en-US}}</ref> Ten percent of sales supported the LGBTQ charity [[GLAAD]].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ \n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Album details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|''[[Pretty Mess (album)|Pretty Mess]]''\n|\n*Released: August 11, 2009\n*Label: [[E1 Entertainment]]\n*Format: CD, digital download\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Single\n! colspan=\"3\" | Peaks\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- \n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\" | [[Dance Club Songs|US<br/>Dance<br/>Club]]<br><ref>{{cite web|title=Erika Jayne Dance Club Songs Chart History|url=https:/